1
00:00:52,343 --> 00:00:53,428
What are you doing, huh?

2
00:00:53,511 --> 00:00:56,306
And what are you doing there
in the secret door of agents? Huh?

3
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:57,640
How did you know that?

4
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,351
I'm the one who told him about it.

5
00:01:00,435 --> 00:01:02,520
But, Mikoy, what are you doing here?

6
00:01:03,813 --> 00:01:05,356
Come here.

7
00:01:07,108 --> 00:01:08,318
I just miss you.

8
00:01:09,027 --> 00:01:11,071
Do you feel the same thing about me?

9
00:01:11,154 --> 00:01:12,197
I'm just joking!

10
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:14,783
Come on! You look so tense.

11
00:01:14,866 --> 00:01:17,660
I'm here because I got fresh information.

12
00:01:17,744 --> 00:01:19,454
This one! Do you all see that?

13
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:23,083
<i>This is where all the files</i>
<i>of Vertex's drivers came from.</i>

14
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:25,752
I cracked down on all
the local operations of the Moraviano.

15
00:01:25,835 --> 00:01:28,213
<i>And I know how to bring them down.</i>

16
00:01:38,848 --> 00:01:39,891
Are you there?

17
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:47,857
Are you there?

18
00:02:18,179 --> 00:02:19,722
What the heck!

19
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:22,642
You're the one acting crazy.

20
00:02:22,725 --> 00:02:24,853
You look like you've seen a ghost.

21
00:02:26,938 --> 00:02:27,772
It's just that…

22
00:02:27,856 --> 00:02:30,233
I got traumatized by what I watched.
What was it?

23
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:32,861
That ‘Taiwan Killer Hospital' thing.
It really traumatized me.

24
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,322
- Why?
- Well, that's what you get

25
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:38,783
for watching stuff like that without me.

26
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:41,619
Sorry, sweetheart. I just got excited.

27
00:02:41,703 --> 00:02:43,496
But I'm free now.

28
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:45,790
Come on, do you want to binge-watch
horror movies together?

29
00:02:46,499 --> 00:02:48,209
Not anymore, sweetheart.

30
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:52,130
Actually, I wanted to ask
for your permission.

31
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:57,302
You don't love me anymore?

32
00:03:03,308 --> 00:03:05,768
You're being so dramatic!

33
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,854
No, it's not that.

34
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:13,151
My dad needs me to fix some things.

35
00:03:17,947 --> 00:03:19,365
So, like what?

36
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:27,707
He doesn't want it neglected.

37
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:30,835
I thought it was something else.

38
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:35,381
So, when are you coming back?

39
00:03:37,258 --> 00:03:38,885
I'm not sure.

40
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:43,389
But one thing I'm sure of…

41
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:45,725
Is that when I come back,

42
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:50,021
we're gonna have the best time ever.

43
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:55,360
Do you want to finally go through
with our travel plans?

44
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:56,486
Really?

45
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:57,946
Yes!

46
00:03:58,029 --> 00:03:59,948
Yes, of course!

47
00:04:00,031 --> 00:04:02,784
Okay, promise me?

48
00:05:31,205 --> 00:05:34,625
Viktor is probably already wondering
why you've been gone for hours.

49
00:05:34,709 --> 00:05:37,253
And if he discovers that
you failed to kill me,

50
00:05:37,336 --> 00:05:39,547
what do you think he'll think of you?

51
00:05:48,389 --> 00:05:49,390
<i>She's right.</i>

52
00:05:56,939 --> 00:05:59,901
So now, I'll show you our target.

53
00:06:11,287 --> 00:06:12,580
I just wanted to try.

54
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:30,098
And it has a delivery scheduled
this Friday at Ignacio Port.

55
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:36,270
Here.

56
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:38,898
I also made my own storyboard

57
00:06:38,981 --> 00:06:42,318
so we'll know and visualize
what could happen.

58
00:06:42,401 --> 00:06:44,862
And based on the information
given by Mikoy,

59
00:06:44,946 --> 00:06:48,449
shipments at Ignacio Port
are consistently delayed by 1-2 hours.

60
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:50,743
Given the loading time,

61
00:06:51,577 --> 00:06:54,831
it shouldn't be far from
the port's 5-10 km radius.

62
00:07:17,603 --> 00:07:19,856
I'll handle the traffic control.

63
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:22,233
I will coordinate with
the local police units

64
00:07:22,316 --> 00:07:24,986
and make sure no one interferes
with our operation.

65
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:35,371
And all we need to do is
seize one cargo container

66
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:36,747
and that should be enough

67
00:07:36,831 --> 00:07:40,543
for us to get a court order
to investigate Vertex.

68
00:07:50,595 --> 00:07:52,096
- Sianong.
- Yes?

69
00:07:55,224 --> 00:07:57,894
I can't find him in his office.
Where is he?

70
00:08:18,998 --> 00:08:20,291
At home.

71
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:22,251
Where else would I go?

72
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:26,672
Dear…

73
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:28,966
Stress doesn't make you beautiful.

74
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:31,594
<i>Do you want to get wrinkles?</i>

75
00:08:35,014 --> 00:08:36,140
<i>Yes, I know you.</i>

76
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:39,977
How can I not worry?

77
00:08:40,061 --> 00:08:42,647
After everything I found out from Sianong.

78
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:44,524
Damn that Sianong.

79
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,025
What did he tell you?

80
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:51,280
How can I protect you
if you're keeping me in the dark?

81
00:08:57,036 --> 00:08:58,871
From the moment I wake up,

82
00:08:58,955 --> 00:09:00,623
every move I make,

83
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:04,126
my feet are already in the grave.

84
00:09:17,431 --> 00:09:21,602
<i>For your future, for all your futures.</i>

85
00:09:21,686 --> 00:09:23,104
Sofie.

86
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:35,032
You have to be strong, dear.

87
00:09:37,076 --> 00:09:38,661
<i>If anything happens to me,</i>

88
00:09:39,203 --> 00:09:41,122
<i>You go to your sister Alex.</i>

89
00:09:47,545 --> 00:09:51,465
<i>And those VHZ tapes under my bed,</i>

90
00:09:51,549 --> 00:09:53,426
dispose of them, okay?

91
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:01,267
I don't care!

92
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:09,775
<i>Don't worry, my dear.</i>

93
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:12,778
We've been through this a lot of times.

94
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:16,824
And I'm still here, standing, fighting.

95
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:19,952
We can't stop our lives from running,

96
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:22,622
just because my life is under threat.

97
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:25,791
<i>And Sofie, what did I tell you?</i>

98
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:29,420
That you're more likely
to die in a car accident,

99
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:30,671
than for enemies to kill you.

100
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:34,634
Because you are still the legendary

101
00:10:35,176 --> 00:10:37,386
‘Sharpshooting Executioner of Mindoro'.

102
00:10:38,888 --> 00:10:41,390
That's right. And remember that.

103
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:44,727
See you later, dear.

104
00:12:20,239 --> 00:12:21,907
Hold on.

105
00:12:21,991 --> 00:12:23,409
Have a seat first.

106
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:25,411
I'm getting tired of looking up at you.

107
00:12:25,494 --> 00:12:28,205
What exactly are you worried about?

108
00:12:44,388 --> 00:12:47,808
That Norberto guy is an easy target.

109
00:13:07,411 --> 00:13:09,413
They're no match for our daughter.

110
00:14:18,148 --> 00:14:19,400
Is this my last hour?

111
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:26,490
Dad?!

112
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:10,784
Dad?!

113
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:21,795
Dad…

114
00:15:22,379 --> 00:15:23,672
what are you doing here?

115
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:24,673
And what's this?

116
00:15:24,757 --> 00:15:26,175
Why did you point your gun at me?

117
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:27,593
It's a test.

118
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:29,762
A test?! Dad, I'm not in school anymore.

119
00:15:29,845 --> 00:15:31,221
Not that kind of test.

120
00:15:31,305 --> 00:15:32,681
And why do you even have a gun?

121
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:36,310
I'm testing you to see if you can handle
what you got yourself into.

122
00:17:05,941 --> 00:17:07,651
Mikoy, I know everything.

123
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:11,822
I also know about
your double life as an asset.

124
00:17:13,741 --> 00:17:16,869
And I also know the true
identity of Viktor Valtrovi.

125
00:17:17,453 --> 00:17:18,412
How?

126
00:17:31,508 --> 00:17:33,427
You look like you're searching
for something.

127
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:38,348
Thanks, but…

128
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:41,810
my wife's frying pan hits
way harder than that.

129
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:43,854
And that's not what I'm buying.

130
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,231
So what are you buying?

131
00:17:46,315 --> 00:17:47,191
Just liquor?

132
00:17:47,775 --> 00:17:49,651
Actually, he's looking for me, Rosa.

133
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:51,779
You have a request in the VIP room.

134
00:17:51,862 --> 00:17:52,863
Go dance there first.

135
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:54,448
Fine, Mama.

136
00:17:55,115 --> 00:17:56,533
So that's your type.

137
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:06,877
The infamous Catacutan.

138
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:14,843
Oh, my gosh!

139
00:18:15,344 --> 00:18:17,096
You go to girly bars?

140
00:18:17,805 --> 00:18:19,890
For me to get an information.

141
00:18:20,641 --> 00:18:22,976
Information? Stop lying!

142
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:24,686
I'm telling Mom about this.

143
00:18:25,729 --> 00:18:26,772
What?

144
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:29,566
You're telling your mom? Try it.

145
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:31,527
Your eyes will be the only thing
without bruises.

146
00:18:31,610 --> 00:18:34,029
Whoa, I was just joking, Dad.

147
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:35,364
You're so harsh.

148
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:37,491
Mikoy, enough joking around.

149
00:18:38,742 --> 00:18:40,160
Tell me everything now,

150
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:41,578
and this time

151
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:43,914
only the truth.

152
00:18:46,083 --> 00:18:48,585
Mikoy, do you even understand
what you've gotten yourself into?

153
00:19:05,894 --> 00:19:07,146
Raise your hands.

154
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,569
So my agents were right…

155
00:19:14,528 --> 00:19:16,113
you really are left-handed.

156
00:19:16,196 --> 00:19:17,739
Face me.

157
00:19:20,576 --> 00:19:21,493
Turn around.

158
00:19:36,341 --> 00:19:38,218
You thought I would be easy to kill?

159
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:41,555
Because of your mistake,

160
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:44,057
you're caught now.

161
00:19:58,322 --> 00:19:59,573
Looks like you can feel it,

162
00:19:59,656 --> 00:20:02,492
that my men have surrounded this place.

163
00:20:03,076 --> 00:20:04,286
This is just bait

164
00:20:05,412 --> 00:20:07,539
to make you think I was alone

165
00:20:08,415 --> 00:20:10,375
and you took the bait.

166
00:20:19,801 --> 00:20:22,971
Bok, relax.
Don't worry, as I said earlier,

167
00:20:23,055 --> 00:20:26,016
the tac teams and Agent Kian
are already there, okay?

168
00:20:26,099 --> 00:20:29,269
They're nearby, and if ever
something bad happens

169
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:32,940
they are always ready to move in
in seconds.

170
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:36,944
Be ready.

171
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:48,997
Now, you have nowhere left to run.

172
00:20:52,709 --> 00:20:55,545
You seem taller than in the report

173
00:20:55,629 --> 00:20:57,506
or maybe I'm mistaken.

174
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:09,851
Maybe it's better not to.

175
00:21:10,435 --> 00:21:12,187
Because once you see my face,

176
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:15,023
you're as good as dead.

177
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:22,030
You're not in position to make threats.

178
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:24,908
You're surrounded.
You have nowhere left to go.

179
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:36,295
You should know that.

180
00:22:10,495 --> 00:22:14,333
That sharp-shooting butcher
is such a stupid bastard.

181
00:22:16,585 --> 00:22:18,420
He told me you weren't involved.

182
00:22:18,503 --> 00:22:19,379
Huh?!

183
00:22:19,463 --> 00:22:21,173
Who's a butcher, Dad?

184
00:22:21,256 --> 00:22:22,257
It's Sianong, right?

185
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:23,967
Mikoy.

186
00:22:25,719 --> 00:22:27,304
There's nothing you can do now,
you're already too deep in.

187
00:22:27,387 --> 00:22:28,972
You have no choice.

188
00:22:29,056 --> 00:22:30,682
You have to finish this.

189
00:22:32,059 --> 00:22:33,310
Mikoy, out of everything,

190
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:35,353
why did you choose this?

191
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:36,897
Why did you agree to it?

192
00:22:37,564 --> 00:22:38,940
I didn't want this, Dad.

193
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:42,027
I was just blackmailed.

194
00:22:42,652 --> 00:22:44,780
Those idiots really used you.

195
00:22:44,863 --> 00:22:46,907
Yes Dad, from the start.

196
00:22:48,283 --> 00:22:50,952
But after I found out
what was really happening,

197
00:22:51,953 --> 00:22:55,415
of course it reached a point where
I made my own choice.

198
00:22:55,499 --> 00:22:57,584
I decided to become a part of this.

199
00:22:57,667 --> 00:22:58,835
Why?

200
00:23:00,212 --> 00:23:02,047
This whole mess is dangerous.

201
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:05,258
What were you thinking? And for what?

202
00:23:05,342 --> 00:23:06,510
For Chiara.

203
00:23:08,595 --> 00:23:10,472
Dad, I want to protect her.

204
00:23:10,555 --> 00:23:12,224
From her family's world.

205
00:23:12,307 --> 00:23:13,517
Protect her?

206
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:15,560
Protect her?!

207
00:23:16,853 --> 00:23:18,688
You really think she knows nothing?

208
00:23:19,272 --> 00:23:22,609
You think Chiara doesn't know
the kind of world her parents live in?

209
00:23:56,268 --> 00:23:57,644
- She got out!
- Medic!

210
00:23:57,727 --> 00:23:59,896
- Medic!
- She escaped!

211
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:00,939
You!

212
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:27,007
Looks like she got
shot her clothes have blood.

213
00:24:29,467 --> 00:24:30,760
We might know her.

214
00:24:33,847 --> 00:24:34,681
This is not Henry.

215
00:24:47,152 --> 00:24:48,195
What's that look on your face?

216
00:24:54,743 --> 00:24:55,994
Why did you tell him?

217
00:25:00,582 --> 00:25:01,499
<i>Are you sure?</i>

218
00:25:01,583 --> 00:25:02,876
<i>Because we found out that you're injured.</i>

219
00:25:05,503 --> 00:25:08,882
It rains, it pours.
It's been one setback after another.

220
00:25:08,965 --> 00:25:10,508
Do I need to know something?

221
00:25:11,468 --> 00:25:13,220
I don't believe it, Dad.

222
00:25:13,303 --> 00:25:14,387
You're wrong about Chiara.

223
00:25:14,471 --> 00:25:16,640
Those kind of syndicates, they're family.

224
00:25:18,558 --> 00:25:20,393
That's why I believe Chiara
knows about it.

225
00:25:20,477 --> 00:25:22,354
And I wouldn't be surprise if one day,

226
00:25:22,437 --> 00:25:25,815
<i>she will inherit the syndicate</i>
<i>her family's running.</i>
